Joshua Olukayode Popoola on Monday emerged as the gubernatorial candidate of the New Nigeria Peoples Party (NNPP) in a primary election held in Ibadan, Oyo State. Popoola was declared the winner when delegates from all the 33 local government areas of the state affirmed his candidature, being the only person who purchased the gubernatorial form. The primary election was witnessed by Resident Electoral Commissioner, Mutiu Agboke, NNPP leader in the southwest, Adebisi Olopoeyan, Mathew Abioye and Ibrahim Ajiboye among others. Popoola while speaking after his emergence, said there will be no room for thuggery in the 2023 elections. According to him, “I want to thank God for bringing us here safely. I want to thank the INEC REC for his admonition. “There will be no room for thuggery in 2023. The work has started. We have to work. I will ensure that youths play a major role in our government”. Agboke while speaking, urged people to shun vote-buying. “Do not buy votes, do not sell votes. All the 18 political parties have a presence in Oyo State. POLL “It will not be business as usual. You cannot profit from manipulation during the elections, you can only profit from your popularity”.